# Adolescent Mental Health — Imagery Policy

## One image, one use (unless you specify otherwise)

Each marketing image filename/URL may appear **at most once** across the entire adolescent-mental-health app.

| Counts once | Does not count toward one-use |
|-------------|-------------------------------|
| Page heroes, section photos, bento/modality images, backgrounds | `logos/` (navbar + footer + OG may share `BRAND_LOGO`) |
| Any `amh_*.jpg` in `site-assets/images/` | Payer logos in `logos/insurance/` (same mark on one page only unless repeated for a logo strip) |

**Do not:**
- Copy an `amh_*` path from one view into another (e.g. sharing `amh_viop_individual05.jpg` on both Virtual IOP and Adolescent IOP pages).
- Reuse a homepage section image on an inner page.
- Point two `<Image>` or `background-image` usages at the same Supabase object URL.

**Only reuse when the user explicitly approves** (e.g. “reuse the Virtual IOP hero on the admissions page”).

### Registry workflow

1. Add every new marketing image to `src/lib/site.ts` (`HOME_IMGS`, `PAGE_IMGS`, or a page-specific export).
2. Before shipping, check for duplicate filenames:

```bash
rg -o 'amh_[a-z0-9_]+\.(jpg|jpeg|webp|png)' apps/adolescent-mental-health/src \
  | sort | uniq -c | sort -rn | awk '$1 > 1'
```

3. Output must be empty (except logos under `logos/`).

Prefer page-local constants only when the image is used on a single route; otherwise centralize in `site.ts` so duplicates are visible in one file.

## WordPress import images are blog-only

Do **not** reference `site-assets/images/wp-migrated/` (or any WordPress migration bucket path) on any route or shared component **except** blog rendering.

| Allowed | Not allowed |
|---------|-------------|
| `/blog`, `/blog/[slug]`, blog post body HTML from `blog_posts` | Homepage, about, contact, treatment/therapy views, nav, footer, LP pages |
| `BlogPostArticle`, `PostBody`, markdown/HTML migrated post content | Hardcoded `next/image` `src`, CSS `background-image`, or constants pointing at `wp-migrated` |

## Required workflow for net-new marketing imagery

1. Generate unique AI images per page/section (on-brand: calm clinical blue `#83B3DC`, teen virtual mental health context).
2. Upload to `site-assets/images/` with naming: `amh_<route-prefix>_<section><index>.jpg` (e.g. `amh_home_why01.jpg`).
3. Reference via `SB_ROOT` / `PAGE_IMGS` in `src/lib/site.ts` — never inline `wp-migrated` URLs.

## Brand assets (logo, payer logos)

- Store under `site-assets/images/logos/` (e.g. `logos/amh-logo.png`, `logos/insurance/aetna.png`).
- Do not pull logos from `wp-migrated` in Navbar, Footer, or marketing pages.
- Payer logos may be relocated official marks — not AI-generated.

## Blog exception

WordPress-migrated featured images and inline `<img>` URLs inside published `blog_posts.content` may remain until those posts are re-imaged individually. Do not copy WP blog images onto new marketing pages.

## PR check

Before shipping adolescent-mental-health page work, run:

```bash
rg 'wp-migrated' apps/adolescent-mental-health/src --glob '!**/blog/**'
```

Zero matches outside blog-specific render paths.
